      A rain of ice slammed into his already badly battered flesh, his vision swam in a sea of fog.... he knew he was going to die.<br>
      Shifting his gaze from his torn side to the beast before him, he felt the rage grow. The fires of his dark soul ignited,his vision cleared instantly, and he stood upright, Slowly he began to move his hands in precise gestures, chanting in a spidery tongue the words of magic. Then the magic came...<br>
      It raced through his body like a twisting inferno, feeding off the fire of his soul, igniting the blaze in his eyes, slowly he drew the fire out to encircle his hands. The blazing energy alive with it's own power. Directing all his hurt, his anger, and desperation into it he hurled the torrent of flame at the great beast...<br>
       It screamed in rage as the flames consumed it, its attention turned for just an instant but that was long enough. The multitude of blows raining down on it from the gathered monks and warriors finished it... the fight was finally over.<br>
     Dropping to his knees the wizard looked at the ground to see Caterlie lying  before him. She was still breathing. That was good, he had been worried when the beast had turned on her its talons slashing, tail snapping out to entangle her. He stared in wonder at the courage of the young enchantress. Far younger than most of the family that was gathered there she stood in the front of the battle casting the first spell, and drawing the attention of the beast. Luckily the Warriors were able to taunt it off her in time, either that or one of the clerics had been able to save her. <br>
     Once again his vision blurred, his time was soon.... Then he heard a clear voice call out. &quot; By the will of the Nameless<br>
you shall be healed by Innoruukk's hand&quot; <br>
     Xavar froze as a warm light seemed to engulf his body. He could feel ribs unbreak, muscle knit itself back together,and flesh regrow over the broken surface. Looking down to what was once a terrible wound, he saw only perfect skin, unmarred by even a scar. From behind him walked Synnovea, a weary smile on her face, her once gleaming armor covered in blood and dirt. Pride burned in her eyes.  <br>
      &quot; You all did very well,&quot; she said &quot; I am proud of you all&quot; her gaze and smile took in everyone gathered there, and one by one, they all broke into smiles, pride gleaming in their eyes as well. Even the Iskar monks laying on the ground in a mock death broke their illusion with a twitch of a smile. Her gaze swept to the beast they had just killed. &quot;Congratulations , you have killed a Dragon....&quot; a mischievous smirk stole across her face &quot; Lets see what we can loot from its horde &quot;<br>
<br>
